<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>No. 1408
                    The Ambassador in France (
                        Caffery
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945Berlinv02</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d1408</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">1408</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-08-06T17:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-08-06T17:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-06T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-06T17:00:00-05:00" n="1408" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1408">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Potsdam/8–745: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1408<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJ1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-07T00:00:00+02:00">August 7, 1945—midnight.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4772. The following is translation of note dated August 4 handed to me by
                        <persName corresp="#p_BG1">Bidault</persName> this evening (my 4769, August
                        7<note n="1" xml:id="d1408fn1">
                        <ref target="#d1405">Document No. 1405</ref>.</note>).</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“Concerning the communications addressed to it on July 31, August 1 and 2 by
                        the three govts represented at the Potsdam Conference,<note n="2" xml:id="d1408fn2">For <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">Caffery</persName>’s
                            notes to <persName corresp="#p_BG1">Bidault</persName> on the results of
                            the Berlin Conference, see <ref target="#d1395">documents Nos.
                                1395</ref>–<ref target="#d1400">1400</ref>.</note> the French
                        Provisional Govt, desirous of avoiding inconveniences (<hi rend="italic">inconvénients</hi>) which have occurred in the past, and noting that
                        the communiqué published at the termination of the Potsdam Conference<note n="3" xml:id="d1408fn3">
                            <ref target="#d1384">Document No. 1384</ref>.</note> treats of questions
                        about which it has not been advised, would like to know if the information
                        which has been furnished up to the present time covers the whole of the
                        results of the conference, or if other important decisions have been made,
                        notably with regard to the multiple problems with which the Council of
                        Ministers of the five great powers will have to deal”.</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
